Both required files are written and the transcript validates against `transcript_schema.json`.

**Top findings across the 25 iterations:**

- A small set of clinical features (`feature_078`, `feature_057`, `log1p(feature_013)`, `feature_006`, `feature_009`, plus a tiny `feature_067` term) explains ~97% of pfs_months variance.
- The dominant "treatment-like" signal is a **synergy between `feature_109` and `feature_039`**: each is null on its own (raw cell means ~3.67–3.74 mo), but the co-occurrence (~1% of the cohort) raises mean PFS to 5.22 mo — interaction coef +1.43 mo, p<1e-300.
- **No outcome disparity by race or insurance.** Univariable ANOVAs are flat (range ≤0.06 mo); after adjustment all demographic indicators have p>0.66.
- **Receipt of the combo is also equal across race and insurance** — no access disparity.
- The *magnitude* of the combo benefit shows statistical heterogeneity across race (combo×race p≤0.001) and insurance (combo×private p~5e-10), but several subgroup cells are small (n=8–58) so direction estimates are unstable.
- Real clinical-by-clinical interactions exist: `feature_078×feature_057`, `feature_078×log(feature_013)`, `feature_057×log(feature_013)`, `feature_009×feature_078`, `feature_006×feature_057` — all reflect attenuation of favorable predictors in higher-severity / higher-burden strata.

Files emitted: `transcript.json` (25 iterations, schema-valid) and `analysis_summary.txt`.
